claim.claim-text:
1. A laser power control arrangement in an electro-optical reader for reading indicia, comprising:
a) a laser for generating a laser beam having an output power;
b) a movable scan component;
c) a drive for moving the scan component for scanning the laser beam across the indicia with a scan line;
d) a monitor for monitoring an operating condition of the reader, and for detecting reader malfunction when the operating condition differs from a preestablished condition; and
e) a controller for controlling the output power of the laser upon detection of the reader malfunction, and for repetitively deenergizing and energizing the laser to flash the scan line on the indicia after the indicia has been read to serve as a visual indicator that the indicia has been successfully read.

4. A laser power control method in an electro-optical reader for reading indicia, comprising the steps of:
a) generating a laser beam having an output power with a laser;
b) scanning the laser beam across the indicia with a scan line;
c) monitoring an operating condition of the reader, and detecting reader malfunction when the operating condition differs from a preestablished condition;
d) controlling the output power of the laser upon detection of the reader malfunction; and
e) repetitively deenergizing and energizing the laser to flash the scan line on the indicia after the indicia has been read to serve as a visual indicator that the indicia has been successfully read.
